Steps needed to set up Vinz Clortho on a new system.  Default logging is into /var/log/vinz_clortho/vinz_clortho.log

1. Create excuting user (e.g. vdatas) with appropriate permissions

2. Make sure /etc/hostname has the correct hostname

3. Make sure there's an appropriate settings section in vinz_clortho for the hostname in (2)

4. Create /var/log/vinz_clortho directory with propermissions for user of (1) to write to

5. Copy vinz-clortho script from this directory into /etc/init.d

6. Inside /etc/init.d/vinz-clortho, Update DAEMON_USER variable to be the user of (1)

7. Run "update-rc.d vinz-clortho defaults" to add the vinz-clortho daemon to the start-up scripts

8. Enable the service with "sudo service vinz-clortho start"